<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-16T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-16T13:00:00-05:00" n="796" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d796">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860m.00/417: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Lithuania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_NOJC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Norem</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kaunas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-16T19:00:00+01:00">November
                                    16, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 17—12:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>65. <persName corresp="#p_BK1">Bizauskas</persName> informed me
                            confidentially that Russian troops are taking garrison positions
                            Wednesday, Thursday, Friday<note n="66" xml:id="d796fn66">November
                                15–17.</note> of this week. President <persName corresp="#p_SA1">Smetona</persName> has asked Merky Mayor of Kaunas, to form a new
                            Cabinet.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_NOJC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Norem</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>